V3-T122|powershell|Write tools/vram_snapshot.ps1 in PowerShell that parses nvidia-smi query output for total, used, and free VRAM plus GPU utilization, appends a timestamped row to logs/vram_history.csv, and prints the current snapshot as a one-line summary.
V3-T123|powershell|Write tools/models_report.ps1 in PowerShell that parses ollama list output into objects with name, size, and modified date, prints them as a sorted table, and exports the same rows to models_report.csv next to the script.
V3-T124|powershell|Write tools/build_all.ps1 in PowerShell that builds the main solution and the SwarmCli project in Release, stops on the first failed build with a red error summary, and ends with a table of produced exe paths and their file sizes in MB.
V3-T125|powershell|Write tools/test_quick.ps1 in PowerShell that runs only the T10 language-detection unit tests via dotnet test with a filter, parses the pass/fail counts from the output, and prints a green PASS or red FAIL line suitable for use as a pre-commit smoke check.
V3-T126|powershell|Write tools/disk_report.ps1 in PowerShell that measures the size of each top-level folder in the workspace, prints the ten largest as a table with sizes in MB, and flags any folder over 1 GB in yellow.
V3-T127|powershell|Write tools/untracked_audit.ps1 in PowerShell that lists git untracked files older than 7 days with their sizes and ages, suggesting per-file whether to commit or ignore based on extension, and supporting -Json for machine-readable output.
V3-T128|powershell|Write tools/env_doctor.ps1 in PowerShell that checks the installed versions of dotnet, python, git, and ollama against minimums defined at the top of the script, printing one PASS or FAIL line per tool and exiting 1 when anything fails.
V3-T129|powershell|Write tools/kill_orphans.ps1 in PowerShell that finds OrchestratorIDE and swarmcli processes whose parent process is gone, stops them after listing what it found, and supports -WhatIf to preview without killing anything.
V3-T130|powershell|Write tools/log_grep.ps1 in PowerShell that searches all files under .orc/swarm/runs/ for a pattern argument, printing matches with two lines of context, the containing file's run id, and a final count of matching runs.
V3-T131|powershell|Write tools/release_notes.ps1 in PowerShell that collects git commits since the most recent tag, groups them by conventional-commit prefix into Added, Fixed, and Changed sections, and writes RELEASE_NOTES_DRAFT.md with the grouped bullets.
V3-T132|powershell|Write tools/startup_bench.ps1 in PowerShell that launches the OrchestratorIDE Release exe three times, measures milliseconds until the main window handle appears using Get-Process MainWindowHandle polling, closes it each time, and prints the three timings with their average.
V3-T133|powershell|Write tools/backup_manifest.ps1 in PowerShell that copies reviewed_v1.json to backups/manifests/reviewed_v1_<timestamp>.json, prunes the folder to the newest 20 copies, and prints the backup path and the count of retained backups.
